    personally-identifying information.
  </p>

  <h3>Cookies</h3>

  <p>
    A cookie is a string of information that a website stores on a
    visitor’s computer, and that the visitor’s browser provides to the
    website each time the visitor returns. atomvote.com uses cookies to
    help atomvote.com identify and track visitors, their usage of
    atomvote.com website, and their website access preferences. atomvote.com
    visitors who do not wish to have cookies placed on their computers
    should set their browsers to refuse cookies before using atomvote.com’s
    websites, with the drawback that certain features of atomvote.com’s
    websites may not function properly without the aid of cookies.
  </p>

